 t > 10^5$). A strong dependence on $\\epsilon$ is also observed\non $\\tau$ and $\\langle {{\\bf q}\\cdot {\\hat e}_\\psi} \\rangle$. The radial\npropagation of pulses in fully chaotic fields considerably slows down in the\nshear reversal region and, as a result, $\\tau$, in reversed shear\nconfigurations is an order of magnitude longer than the one in monotonic\n$q$-profiles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Sep 2014 17:58:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-09-11"}
