displays a more complex age-metallicity relation\nstarting from low metallicity and a sequence in alpha-element abundances with a\nslope much steeper than observed in the old episode, starting from [Fe/H]=-1.8\ndex and [Mg/Fe]~0.4 dex and declining to Mg-poor values ([Mg/Fe]<-0.5 dex).\nThis indicates clearly that both episodes of star formation formed from gas\nwith different abundance patterns, inconsistent with simple evolution in an\nisolated system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Sep 2014 20:00:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-11-19"}
